# Service configuration - kdb products

Original URL: https://code.kx.com/insights/enterprise/configuration/service.html

# Service configuration

Configuration for a chart Service resource is configurable at a chart level.

Each chart's Service object shares the same configurable fields e.g. `type`
`annotations`.

    
    
    service:
      type: ClusterIP
      port: 8080
      annotations:
        custom: annotation
        anothercustom: annotation
    

These fields are used to populate the Service resource at deploy time.

## type

The Service type, `ClusterIP`, `LoadBalancer` or `NodePort`.

Variable | Type | Example  
---|---|---  
`type` | `string` | `ClusterIP`  
  
## port

The Port to expose via the Service.

Variable | Type | Example  
---|---|---  
`port` | `integer` | `8080`  
  
## annotations

The `annotations` field allows a user to append key-value annotations to the
Service resource.

Variable | Type | Example  
---|---|---  
`annotations` | `object` | `{ "custom": "annotation" }`

